quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  8,20,"O believers, obey God and His Messenger, and do not turn away from Him, even as you are listening"
  8,21,"and be not as those who say, 'We hear,' and they hear not"
  8,22,Surely the worst of beasts in God's sight are those that are deaf and dumb and do not understand
  8,23,"If God had known of any good in them He would have made them hear; and if He had made them hear, they would have turned away, swerving aside"
  8,24,"O believers, respond to God and the Messenger when He calls you unto that which will give you life; and know that God stands between a man and his heart, and that to Him you shall be mustered"
  8,25,And fear a trial which shall surely not smite in particular the evildoers among you; and know that God is terrible in retribution
  8,26,"And remember when you were few and abased in the land, and were fearful that the people would snatch you away; but He gave you refuge, and confirmed you with His help, and provided you with the good things, that haply you might be thankful"
  8,27,"O believers, betray not God and the Messenger, and betray not your trusts and that wittingly"
  8,28,"and know that your wealth and your children are a trial, and that with God is a mighty wage"